				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">In fact aside of Battletoads, it was extremely uncommon to use such as "slot" system on the NES, as opposed to what is seen on other systems. The low ROM-&gt;VRAM bandwith is the reason for this.
<br />99% of games just have banks of graphics which are loaded once in a level, or that are switched as animations need to change, such as in SMB3, allowing for more a detailed main character and / or more main characters.</div>

					
